<subSubSection id="F021F30E32F38DEB9D6E07F50BA285FA" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C1D9044B25CD2A03F74D530111769098" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9497BF859A3A682B13D2647E2108FCC" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">
<taxonomicName id="93E8B46ADB1BBE14C9A3F8D149887723" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia beyrichiana" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beyrichiana">
<emphasis id="29A52BF138CBFEE3C34947558BFBC0F9" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Muhlenbergia beyrichiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur in Brazil, Ecuador and Peru. Earlier, it was reported in Mexico and Central America but these are probably an error for 
<taxonomicName id="D29A3551EC3E0DA27AF3E14D85A54216" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia diandra" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diandra">
<emphasis id="C6A599195CA2E1E13DD2DC961D5E34BD" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Muhlenbergia diandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(R.W. Pohl) Columbus, a more recently described species that superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="0C985D9AE7E2131C2A8058E5EF535AC8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. beyrichiana" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="beyrichiana">
<emphasis id="3CCB68416951833D62F681DD7ECC8FB7" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">M. beyrichiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Espejo Serna et al. 2000; 
<bibRefCitation id="ABABD2EAF4D157C217873BC273E35B24" author="Laegaard, S" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B17" refString="Laegaard, S, Peterson, PM, 2001. 214(2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1-131." title="214 (2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1 - 131." year="2001">
<normalizedToken id="F96C7ECECE2164D1B65C1B9E6C789DE5" originalValue="LÃ¦gaard">Laegaard</normalizedToken>
and Peterson 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="86D127E377A0B7B7B07BABE5783EA5A3" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B34" refString="Peterson, PM, Soreng, RJ, Davidse, G, Filgueiras, TS, Zuloaga, FO, Judziewicz, EJ, 2001. Catalogue of New World grasses (Poaceae): II. subfamily Chloridoideae. Contributions from the United States National Herbarium 41: 1 - 255" title="Catalogue of New World grasses (Poaceae): II. subfamily Chloridoideae." volume="41" year="2001">Peterson et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B99104A0D429CA09EB7A545A5E845EBC" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="40AF14DBF074E9297FCE2AD41899897F" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FE13EA30397D42526B97E65104F6984E" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">
This species occurs in xerophilic savannahs with 
<taxonomicName id="3CFA1C4A47A090BE5F3DE09A650664FA" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cactaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Cactales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Cactaceae</taxonomicName>
, roadsides and along moist ravines; 150-2000 m (
<bibRefCitation id="71E5C53D36AAF2826B8449CCEEB44636" author="Laegaard, S" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B17" refString="Laegaard, S, Peterson, PM, 2001. 214(2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1-131." title="214 (2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1 - 131." year="2001">
