<subSubSection id="2262604FBA24897EF267900A0F0202C4" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="135" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" type="comments">
<paragraph id="D77E398DA7464AC4A7F3C8EB59217661" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A4FDB269407B31FFE2C4CB7A368A54D7" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">
<taxonomicName id="1A80254579CBFA1B728C4910B5D85CFE" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia beyrichiana" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beyrichiana">
<emphasis id="51C13E9D41D074848DB9943BBB3BFE53" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">Muhlenbergia beyrichiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="920692964478A0021F3C83EEFD77525A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. pereilema" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pereilema">
<emphasis id="3BC1E1398956E4F90B29F51E448B5ADC" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">M. pereilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
P.M. Peterson, which does not occur in Peru, but can be separated from the latter in having interrupted 
<emphasis id="46F5C1AC9459A4C487FCE1EBB7F380DB" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">panicles</emphasis>
with divergent primary branches (versus uninterruped 
<emphasis id="A88F4E527C393F9610CF0B9317556935" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">panicles</emphasis>
with tightly appressed primary branches in 
<taxonomicName id="E1970E2E480201EDF5BA83652E20BAD3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. pereilema" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="134" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pereilema">
<emphasis id="97CB490A73F2F19B7B53BF069B68EE2F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="134">M. pereilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), straight lemma awns (versus flexuous or wavy), wide leaf blades 3-6 (-8) mm (versus 2-3 mm) and ciliate auricles (versus not ciliate) [
<bibRefCitation id="A67761FBA243C4A407EB2DA3989578BB" author="Laegaard, S" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the United States National Herbarium" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B17" refString="Laegaard, S, Peterson, PM, 2001. 214(2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1-131." title="214 (2). Gramineae (part 2) Subfam. Chloridoideae. In: Harling G, Andersson L (Eds) Botanical Institute, University of Goeteborg, Goeteborg, 1 - 131." year="2001">
<normalizedToken id="235C60F5BE4FDCD88E091B6526650640" originalValue="LÃ¦gaard">Laegaard</normalizedToken>
and Peterson 2001
</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6A105F5DBA9279D1C0B9307F34A949EA" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName id="24920723BC547B59A691E7989210C03F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia beyrichiana" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="beyrichiana">
<emphasis id="42225430068290DD0E516FF3A7099D36" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">
<pageBreakToken id="D25DF5C10300C487B01296421004F0C1" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" start="start">Muhlenbergia</pageBreakToken>
beyrichiana
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in a clade with 
<taxonomicName id="C5549BF3BA9B1FEF1DFBBC44E2D34B53" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. pereilema" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pereilema">
<emphasis id="9CA612F13D93501D9533934D0813CF67" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">M. pereilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B4EF114850910A4183DB0F3792C8340D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. plumiseta" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="plumiseta">
<emphasis id="50E0B7FF40B98BEC4D0790ACE943651D" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">M. plumiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="8359CCFEDCD4A7E755AFEE419E75E778" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. flexuosa" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis id="5FFBE894292DEA652DDF970817328CDF" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">M. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hitchc. in 
<taxonomicName id="A1C071C786E78109A65F9C4E67F64CCF" authority="subg. Muhlenbergia" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="135" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Muhlenbergia">M. subg. Muhlenbergia</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A7B99322F3B8F4FF08E6630C352844FC" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A, B Maximum-likelihood tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in red occur in South America; scale bar = 2 %." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254042" pageId="12" pageNumber="135">1B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="66CA5120A468C5E2FD1F8F8E0813AC26" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" pagination="1532 - 1554" refId="B38" refString="Peterson, PM, Romaschenko, K, Johnson, G, 2010b. A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences. American Journal of Botany 97 (9): 1532 - 1554, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" title="A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" volume="97" year="2010 b">Peterson et al. 2010b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
